Problem: Find the maximum and minimum elements in an array of integers.

Constraints:
1. The array can have a maximum of 10^6 elements.
2. The array can have both positive and negative integers.

Solution:

```java
public class MaxMinInArray {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] arr = {4, 7, -2, 9, 5, 1, -6, 3};

        // Initialize max and min as the first element of the array
        int max = arr[0];
        int min = arr[0];

        // Loop through the array to find the maximum and minimum elements
        for (int i = 1; i < arr.length; i++) {
            if (arr[i] > max) {
                max = arr[i];
            } else if (arr[i] < min) {
                min = arr[i];
            }
        }

        // Print the maximum and minimum elements
        System.out.println("Maximum element: " + max);
        System.out.println("Minimum element: " + min);
    }
}
```

In this solution, we initialize variables `max` and `min` with the first element of the array. Then, we iterate through the array and update `max` and `min` if we find a larger or smaller element. Finally, we print the maximum and minimum elements after the loop.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) where n is the number of elements in the array. This is because we iterate through the array once to find the maximum and minimum elements.

